question.text: A cyclist riding the bicycle at a speed of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>14</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>m </mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> takes a turn around a circular road of radius <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></math> without skidding. Given <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9.8 </mn><mi>m </mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> What is his inclination to the vertical ?

solution.text: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced separators="|"><mfrac><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced open="[" close="]" separators="|"><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>14</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mn>9.8</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>[</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>]</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math>
